In a press conference, President Biden announced that Vice President Kamala Harris would be leading efforts to address migration from Mexico and the Northern Triangle countries. He highlighted the importance of dealing with the root causes of migration and mentioned that the previous administration had eliminated funding for programs aimed at addressing these issues. President Biden expressed confidence in Vice President Harris's ability to lead this effort, citing her experience as a former Attorney General of California. Vice President Harris acknowledged the challenging nature of the situation and emphasized the need to enforce the law while also addressing the root causes of migration. She expressed her intention to engage in diplomacy with the governments, private sector, and civil society of El Salvador, Guatemala, and Honduras to strengthen democracy, the rule of law, and shared prosperity in the region. Vice President Harris also mentioned collaboration with Mexico and other countries in the Western hemisphere and expressed her willingness to work with members of Congress who share the perspective on addressing the root causes of migration.